obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (23254)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23254&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indira Gandhi National Open`
  line `University Act, 1985.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 20th September, 1985, vide notification No. S.O. 678(E), dated 19th September, 1985, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (23255)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23255&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, and the Statutes made hereunder, unless the context otherwise`
  line `requires,"`
  line
  line `(a) "Academic Council" means the Academic Council of the University;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board of Management" means the Board of Management of the University;`
  line
  line `(c) "Board of Recognition" means the Board of Recognition of the University;`
  line
  line `(d) "College" means a College or other academic institution established or maintained by, or`
  line `admitted to the privileges of, the University;`
  line
  line `(e) "distance education system" means the system of imparting education through any means of`
  line `communication, such as broadcasting, telecasting, correspondence courses, seminars, contact`
  line `programmes or the combination of any two or more of such means;`
  line
  line `(f) "employee" means any person appointed by the University, and includes teachers and other`
  line `academic staff of the University;`
  line
  line `(g) "Finance Committee" means the Finance Committee of the University;`
  line
  line `(h) "Governing Body", in relation to a College, means any body (by whatever name called)`
  line `charged with the management of the affairs of the College and recognised as such by the University;`
  line
  line `(i) "Planning Board" means the Planning Board of the University;`
  line
  line `(j) "Regional Centre" means a centre established or maintained by the University for the purpose`
  line `of co-ordinating and supervising the work of Study Centres in any region and for performing such`
  line `other functions as may be conferred on such centre by the Board of Management;`
  line
  line `(k) "Regulations" means the Regulations made by any authority of the University under this Act`
  line `for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(l) "School" means a School of Studies of the University;`
  line
  line `(m) "Statutes" and "Ordinances" mean, respectively, the Statutes and Ordinances of the`
  line `University for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(n) "student" means a student of the University, and includes any person who has enrolled`
  line `himself for pursuing any course of study of the University;`
  line
  line `(o) "Study Centre" means a centre established, maintained or recognised by the University for the`
  line `purpose of advising, counselling or for rendering any other assistance required by the students;`
  line
  line `(p) "teachers" means Professors, Readers, Lecturers and such other persons as may be designated`
  line `as such by the Ordinances for imparting instruction in the University or for giving guidance or`
  line `rendering assistance to students for pursuing any course of study of the University;`
  line
  line `(q) "University" means the Indira Gandhi National Open University established under this Act;`
  line
  line `(r) "Vice-Chancellor" and "Pro-Vice-Chancellor" mean, respectively, the Vice-Chancellor and a`
  line `Pro-Vice-Chancellor of the University.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (23256)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Proviso added by Act 32 of 1997, s. 2 (w.e.f. 29-8-1997).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23256&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be established a University`
  line `by the name of "the Indira Gandhi National Open University".`
  line
  line `(2) The headquarters of the University shall be at Delhi and it may establish or maintain Colleges,`
  line `Regional Centres and Study Centres at such other places in India as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that the University may, with the prior approval of the Visitor, also establish Study`
  line `Centres outside India.]`
  line
  line `(3) The first Vice-Chancellor, the first Pro-Vice-Chancellors and the first members of the Board of`
  line `Management, the Academic Council and the Planning Board and all persons who may hereafter become`
  line `such officers or members, so long as they continue to hold such office or membership, are hereby`
  line `constituted a body corporate by the name of "the Indira Gandhi National Open University".`
  line
  line `(4) The University shall have perpetual succession and a common seal and shall sue and be sued by`
  line `the said name.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (23257)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `The objects of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23257&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The objects of the University shall be to advance and disseminate`
  line `learning and knowledge by a diversity of means, including the use of any communication technology, to`
  line `provide opportunities for higher education to a larger segment of the population and to promote the`
  line `educational well being of the community generally, to encourage the Open University and distance`
  line `education systems in the educational pattern of the country and to co-ordinate and determine the standards`
  line `in such systems, and the University shall, in organising its activities, have due regard to the objects`
  line `specified in the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (23258)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23258&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The University shall have the following powers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) to provide for instruction in such branches of knowledge, technology, vocations and`
  line `professions as the University may determine from time to time and to make provision for research;`
  line
  line `(ii) to plan and prescribe courses of study for degrees, diplomas, certificates or for any other`
  line purpose;
  line
  line `(iii) to hold examinations and confer degrees, diplomas, certificates or other academic`
  line `distinctions or recognitions on persons who have pursued a course of study or conducted research in`
  line `the manner laid down by the Statutes and Ordinances;`
  line
  line `(iv) to confer honorary degrees or other distinctions in the manner laid down by the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(v) to determine the manner in which distance education in relation to the academic`
  line `programmes of the University may be organised;`
  line
  line `(vi) to institute professorships, readerships, lecturerships and other academic positions`
  line `necessary for imparting instruction or for preparing educational material or for conducting other`
  line `academic activities, including guidance, designing and delivery of course and evaluation of the`
  line `work done by the students, and to appoint persons to such professorships, readerships, lecturerships`
  line `and other academic positions;`
  line
  line `(vii) to co-operate with, and seek the co-operation of, other universities and institutions of`
  line `higher learning, professional bodies and organisations for such purposes as the University considers`
  line necessary;
  line
  line `(viii) to institute and award fellowships, scholarships, prizes and such other awards for`
  line `recognition of merit as the University may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(ix) to establish and maintain such Regional Centres as may be determined by the University`
  line `from time to time;`
  line
  line `(x) to establish, maintain or recognise Study Centres in the manner laid down by the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(xi) to provide for the preparation of instructional materials, including films, cassettes, tapes,`
  line `video cassettes and other software;`
  line
  line `(xii) to organise and conduct refresher courses, workshops, seminars and other programmes for`
  line `teachers, lesson writers, evaluators and other academic staff;`
  line
  line `(xiii) to recognise examinations of, or periods of study (whether in full or part) at, other`
  line `universities, institutions or other places of higher learning as equivalent to examinations or periods`
  line `of study in the University, and to withdraw such recognition at any time;`
  line
  line `(xiv) to make provision for research and development in educational technology and related`
  line matters;
  line
  line `(xv) to create administrative, ministerial and other necessary posts and to make appointments`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(xvi) to receive benefactions, donations and gifts and to acquire, hold, maintain and dispose of`
  line `any property movable or immovable, including trust and Government property, for the purposes of`
  line `the University;`
  line
  line `(xvii) to borrow, with the approval of the Central Government, whether on the security of the`
  line `property of the University or otherwise, money for the purposes of the University;`
  line
  line `(xviii) to enter into, carry out, vary or cancel contracts;`
  line
  line `(xix) to demand and receive such fees and other charges as may be laid down by the`
  line Ordinances;
  line
  line `(xx) to provide, control and maintain discipline among the students and all categories of`
  line `employees and to lay down the conditions of service of such employees, including their codes of`
  line conduct;
  line
  line `(xxi) to recognise any institution of higher learning or studies for such purposes as the`
  line `University may determine and to withdraw such recognition;`
  line
  line `(xxii) to appoint, either on contract or otherwise, visiting Professors, Emeritus Professors,`
  line `Consultants, fellows, scholars, artists, course writers and such other persons who may contribute to`
  line `the advancement of the objects of the University;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) to recognise persons working in other universities, institutions or organisations as`
  line `teachers of the University on such terms and conditions as may be laid down by the Ordinances;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) to determine standards and to specify conditions for the admission of students to courses`
  line `of study of the University which may include examination, evaluation and any other method of`
  line testing;
  line
  line `(xxv) to make arrangements for the promotion of the general health and welfare of the`
  line employees;
  line
  line `(xxvi) to confer autonomous status on a College or a Regional Centre in the manner laid down`
  line `by the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(xxvii) to admit to its privileges any College in or outside India subject to such conditions as`
  line `may be laid down by the Statutes:`
  line
  line `Provided that no College shall be so admitted except with the prior approval of the Visitor;`
  line
  line `(xxviii) to do all such acts as may be necessary or incidental to the exercise of all or any of the`
  line `powers of the University as are necessary and conducive to the promotion of all or any of the`
  line `objects of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, but without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), it shall be the duty of the University to take all such steps as`
  line `it may deem fit for the promotion of the open university and distance education systems and for the`
  line `determination of standards of teaching, evaluation and research in such systems, and for the purpose of`
  line `performing this function, the University shall have such powers, including the power to allocate and`
  line `disburse grants to Colleges, whether admitted to its privileges or not, or to any other university or`
  line `institution of higher learning, as may be specified by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (23259)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Added by Act 32 of 1997, s. 3, for "whole of India" (w.e.f. 29-8-1997).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23259&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The University shall in the exercise of its powers have jurisdiction over the whole`
  line `of India ^1`
  line `[and to the Study Centres outside India].`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (23260)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `University open to all classes, castes and creeds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23260&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The University shall be open to persons of`
  line `either sex and of whatever race, creed, caste or class, and it shall not be lawful for the University to adopt`
  line `or impose on any person any test whatsoever of religious belief or profession in order to entitle him to be`
  line `appointed as a teacher of the University or to hold any other office therein or admitted as a student in the`
  line `University, or to graduate thereat, or to enjoy or exercise any privilege thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to prevent the University from making any special`
  line `provision for the appointment or admission of women or of persons belonging to the weaker sections of`
  line `the society, and in particular, of persons belonging to the Scheduled Castes or Scheduled Tribes.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (23261)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `The Visitor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23261&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of India shall be the Visitor of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4), the Visitor shall have the right to cause an`
  line `inspection to be made, by such person or persons as he may direct, of the University, its buildings,`
  line `laboratories and equipment, and of any College, Regional Centre, a Study Centre and also of the`
  line `examination, instruction and other work conducted or done by the University, and to cause an inquiry to`
  line `be made in like manner in respect of any matter connected with the administration and finances of the`
  line University.
  line
  line `(3) The Visitor shall, in every case, give notice to the University of his intention to cause an`
  line `inspection or inquiry to be made and the University shall, on receipt of such notice, have the right to`
  line `make, within thirty days from the date of receipt of the notice or such other period as the Visitor may`
  line `determine, such representations to him as it may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) After considering the representations, if any, made by the University, the Visitor may cause to be`
  line `made such inspection or inquiry as is referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) Where an inspection or inquiry has been caused to be made by the Visitor, the University shall be`
  line `entitled to appoint a representative who shall have the right to appear in person and to be heard on such`
  line `inspection or inquiry.`
  line
  line `(6) The Visitor may address the Vice-Chancellor with reference to the results of such inspection or`
  line `inquiry together with such views and advice with regard to the action to be taken thereon as the Visitor`
  line `may be pleased to offer and on receipt of the address made by the Visitor, the Vice-Chancellor shall`
  line `communicate forthwith to the Board of Management the results of the inspection or inquiry and the views`
  line `of the Visitor and the advice tendered by him upon the action to be taken thereon.`
  line
  line `(7) The Board of Management shall communicate through the Vice-Chancellor to the Visitor such`
  line `action, if any, as it proposes to take or has been taken by it upon the results of such inspection or inquiry.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the Board of Management does not within a reasonable time, take action to the satisfaction`
  line `of the Visitor, the Visitor may, after considering any explanation furnished or representation made by the Board of Management, issue such directions as he may think fit and any Board of Management shall be`
  line `bound to comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(9) Without prejudice to the foregoing Provision s of this section, the Visitor may, by an order in`
  line `writing, annul any proceedings of the University which is not in conformity with this Act, the Statutes or`
  line `the Ordinances:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any such order, he shall call upon the University to show cause way such`
  line `an order should not be made and, if any cause is shown within a reasonable time, he shall consider the`
  line same.
  line
  line `(10) The Visitor shall have such other powers as may be specified by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (23262)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Officers of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23262&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be the officers of the University:--`
  line
  line `(1) The Vice-Chancellor;`
  line
  line `(2) The Pro-Vice-Chancellors;`
  line
  line `(3) The Directors;`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrars;`
  line
  line `(5) The Finance Officer; and`
  line
  line `(6) Such other officers as may be declared by the Statutes to be the officers of the University.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (23263)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `The Vice-Chancellor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23263&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Vice-Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor in such`
  line `manner, for such term and on such emoluments and other conditions of service as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The Vice-Chancellor shall be the principle academic and executive officer of the University, and`
  line `shall exercise supervision and control over the affairs of the University and give effect to the decisions of`
  line `the all the authorities of the University.`
  line
  line `(3) The Vice-Chancellor may, if he is of the opinion that immediate action is necessary on any matter,`
  line `exercise any power conferred on any authority of the University by or under this Act and shall report to`
  line `such authority the action taken by him on such matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the authority concerned is of the opinion that such action ought not to have been`
  line `taken, it may refer the matter to the Visitor whose decision thereon shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any person in the service of the University who is aggrieved by the action taken`
  line `by the Vice-Chancellor under this sub-section, shall have the right to appeal against such action to the`
  line `Board of Management within ninety days from the date on which such action is communicated to him and`
  line `thereupon the Board of Management may confirm, modify or reverse the action taken by the`
  line Vice-Chancellor.
  line
  line `(4) The Vice-Chancellor, if he in of the opinion that any decision of any authority is beyond the`
  line `powers of the authority conferred by the provisions of this Act, Statutes or Ordinances or that any`
  line `decision taken is not in the interests of the University, may ask the authority concerned to review its`
  line `decision within sixty days of such decision and if the authority refuses to review its decision either in`
  line `whole or in part or no decision is taken by it within the said period of sixty days, the matter shall be`
  line `referred to the Visitor whose decision thereon shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that the decision of the authority concerned shall remain suspended during the period of`
  line `review of such decision by the authority or the Visitor, as the case may be, under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(5) The Vice-Chancellor shall exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes and the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (23264)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `The Pro-Vice-Chancellors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23264&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every Pro-Vice-Chancellor shall be appointed in such manner, on`
  line `such emoluments and other conditions of service, and shall exercise such powers and perform such`
  line `functions, as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (23265)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `The Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23265&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Every Director shall be appointed in such manner, on such emoluments and`
  line `other conditions of service, and shall exercise such powers and perform such functions, as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (23266)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `The Registrars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23266&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Registrar shall be appointed in such manner, on such emoluments`
  line `and other conditions of service as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) A Registrar empowered by the Board of Management shall have the power to enter into, and sign,`
  line `agreements and authenticate records on behalf of the University.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Registrar shall exercise such powers and perform such functions as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (23267)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `The Finance Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23267&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Finance Officer shall be appointed in such manner, on such`
  line `emoluments and other conditions of service and shall exercise such powers and perform such functions as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (23268)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23268&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The manner of appointment, emoluments, powers and duties of the other`
  line `officers of the University shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (23269)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Authorities of the University`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=23269&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be the authorities of the University:--`
  line
  line `(1) The Board of Management;`
  line
  line `(2) The Academic Council;`
  line
  line `(3) The Planning Board;`
  line
  line `(4) The Board of Recognition;`
  line
  line `(5) The Schools of Studies;`
  line
  line `(6) The Finance Committee; and`
  line
  line `(7) Such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the`
  line University.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (28522)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `The Board of Management`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28522&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Management shall be the principal executive`
  line `body of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution of the Board of Management, the term of office of its members and its powers`
  line `and functions shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (28523)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `The Academic Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28523&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Academic Council shall be the principal academic body of the`
  line `University and shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and Ordinances, have the control`
  line `and general regulation of, and be responsible for, the maintenance of standards of learning, education,`
  line `instruction, evaluation and examination within the University and shall exercise such other powers and`
  line `perform such other functions as may be conferred or imposed upon it by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution of the Academic Council and the term of office of its members shall be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (28524)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `The Planning Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28524&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Planning Board of the University which`
  line `shall be the principal planning body of the University and shall also be responsible for the monitoring of`
  line `the developments of the University on the lines indicated in the objects of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution of the Planning Board, the term of office of its members and its powers and`
  line `functions shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (28525)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `The Board of Recognition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28525&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Recognition shall be responsible for admitting`
  line `Colleges to the privileges of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution and the other powers and functions of the Board of Recognition shall be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (28526)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `The Schools of Studies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28526&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be such number of Schools of Studies as the University`
  line `may determine from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution, powers and functions of the Schools of Studies shall be prescribed by the`
  line Statutes.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (28527)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `The Finance Committee`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28527&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The constitution, powers and functions of the Finance Committee`
  line `shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (28528)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Other authorities`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28528&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The constitution, powers and functions of the other authorities which may`
  line `be declared by the Statutes to be authorities of the University shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (28529)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28529&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of appointment of the Vice-Chancellor, the term of his appointment, the`
  line `emoluments and other conditions of his service and the powers and functions that may be exercised`
  line `and performed by him;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of appointment of Pro-Vice-Chancellors, Director, Registrars, the Finance Officer`
  line `and other officers, the emoluments and other conditions of their service and the powers and functions`
  line `that may be exercised and performed by each of the officers;`
  line
  line `(c) the constitution of the Board of Management and other authorities of the University, the terms`
  line `of office of the members of such authorities and the powers and functions that may be exercised and`
  line `performed by such authorities;`
  line
  line `(d) the appointment of teachers and other employees of the University, their emoluments and`
  line `other conditions of service;`
  line
  line `(e) the constitution of a pension or provident fund and the establishment of an insurance scheme`
  line `for the benefit of the employees of the University;`
  line
  line `(f) the principles governing the seniority of service of the employees of the University;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure in relation to any appeal or application for review by any employee or student`
  line `of the University against the action of any officer or authority of the University, including the time`
  line `within which such appeal or application for review shall be preferred or made;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure for the settlement of disputes between the employees or students of the`
  line `University, and the University;`
  line
  line `(i) the conferment of autonomous status on Colleges and Study Centres;`
  line
  line `(j) the co-ordination and determination of standards in the open University and distance education`
  line `systems and the allocation and disbursement of grants to Colleges and other universities and`
  line institutions;
  line
  line `(k) the conditions that are required to be fulfilled for admission of the Colleges to the privileges`
  line `of the University;`
  line
  line `(l) all other matters which by this Act are to be, or may be, provided by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (28530)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Statutes how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28530&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The first Statutes are those set out in the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board of Management may, from time to time, make new or additional Statutes or may`
  line `amend or repeal the Statutes referred to in sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board of Management shall not make, amend or repeal any Statute affecting the`
  line `status, powers or constitution of any authority of the University until such authority has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to express its opinion in writing on the proposed changes and any opinion so`
  line `expressed has been considered by the Board of Management.`
  line
  line `(3) Every new Statute or addition to the Statutes or any amendment or repeal thereof shall require the`
  line `approval of the Visitor, who may assent thereto or withhold assent or remit to the Board of Management`
  line `for re-consideration in the light observations, if any, made by him.`
  line
  line `(4) A new Statute or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall not be valid unless it`
  line `has been assented to by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub-sections, the Visitor may make new or`
  line `additional Statutes or amend or repeal the Statutes referred to in sub-section (1), during the period of three`
  line `years immediately after the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub-sections, the Visitor may direct the`
  line `University to make provisions in the Statutes in respect of any matter specified by him and if the Board of`
  line `Management is unable to implement such a direction within sixty days of its receipt, the Visitor may,`
  line `after considering the reasons, if any, communicated by the Board of Management for its inability to`
  line `comply with such direction, make or amend the Statutes suitably.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (28531)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28531&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of students, the courses of study and the fees therefor, the qualifications`
  line `pertaining to degrees, diplomas, certificates and other courses, the conditions for the grant of`
  line `fellowships, awards and the like;`
  line
  line `(b) the conduct of examinations, including the terms and conditions and appointment of`
  line examiners;
  line
  line `(c) the management of Colleges admitted to the privileges of the University; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which by this Act or the Statutes is to be, or may be, provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
  line
  line `(2) The first Ordinances shall be made by the Vice-Chancellor with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government and the Ordinances so made may be amended, repealed or added to at any time by`
  line `the Board of Management in the manner prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (28532)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title Regulations.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28532&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The authorities of the University may make Regulations consistent with this Act,`
  line `the Statutes and the Ordinances for the conduct of their own business and that of the committees, if any,`
  line `appointed by them and not provided for by this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances in the manner`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (28533)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28533&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual report of the University shall be prepared under the directions of`
  line `the Board of Management which shall include, among other matters, the steps taken by the University`
  line `towards the fulfilment of its objects.`
  line
  line `(2) The annual report so prepared shall be submitted to the Visitor on or before such date as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the annual report, as prepared under sub-section (1) shall also be submitted to the`
  line `Central Government which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before both the Houses of`
  line Parliament.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (28534)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Annual accounts, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28534&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual accounts and the balance-sheet of the University shall be`
  line `prepared under the directions of the Board of Management and shall, once at least every year, and at`
  line `intervals of not more than fifteen months, be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `such person or persons as he may authorise in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the accounts together with the audit report shall be submitted to the Visitor along with`
  line `the observations, if any, of the Board of Management.`
  line
  line `(3) Any observations made by the Visitor on the annual accounts shall be brought to notice of the`
  line `Board of Management and the views of the Board of Management, if any, on such observations shall be`
  line `submitted to the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of the accounts together with the audit report, as submitted to the Visitor, shall also be`
  line `submitted to the Central Government, which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before`
  line `both the Houses of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(5) The audited annual accounts, after having been laid before both the Houses of Parliament, shall be`
  line `published in the Gazette of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (28535)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Conditions of service of employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28535&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every employee of the University shall be appointed`
  line `under a written contract and such contract shall not be inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `Statutes and the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(2) The contract referred to in sub-section (1) shall be lodged with the University and a copy of which`
  line `shall be furnished to the employee concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (28536)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28536&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any dispute arising out of a contract of employment referred to in`
  line `section 30 between the University and an employee shall, at the request of either party, be referred to a`
  line `Tribunal of Arbitration which shall consist of one member nominated by the Board of Management, one`
  line `member nominated by the employee concerned and an umpire to be nominated by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such reference shall be deemed to be a submission to arbitration upon the terms of this`
  line `section within the meaning of the Arbitration Act, 1940 (2 of 1940), and all the provisions of that Act,`
  line `with the exception of section 2 thereof, shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) The procedure for regulating the work of the Tribunal of Arbitration shall be prescribed by the`
  line Statutes.
  line
  line `(4) The decision of the Tribunal of Arbitration shall be final and binding on the parties, and no suit`
  line `shall lie in any court in respect of the matters decided by the Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (28537)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Provident and pension funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28537&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The University shall constitute for the benefit of the`
  line `employees such provident or pension funds or provide such insurance schemes as it may deem fit in such`
  line `manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such provident or pension fund has been so constituted, the Central Government may`
  line `declare that the provisions of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925) shall apply to such funds, as if`
  line `it were a Government Provident Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (28538)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Disputes as to the constitution of the University authorities and bodies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28538&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `If any question`
  line `arises as to whether any person has been duly elected or appointed as, or is entitled to be a member of any`
  line `authority or other body of the University, the matter shall be referred to the Visitor whose decision`
  line `thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (28539)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Filling of casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28539&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `All the casual vacancies among the members (other than ex officio`
  line `members) of any authority or other body of the University shall be filled, as soon as may be convenient,`
  line `by the person or body who appoints elects or co-opts the member whose place has become vacant and any`
  line `person appointed, elected or co-opted to a casual vacancy shall be a member of such authority or body for`
  line `the residue of the term for which the person whose place he fills would have been a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (28540)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Proceedings of the University authorities or bodies not invalidated by vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28540&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `No act or`
  line `proceedings of any authority or any other body shall be invalidated merely by reason of the existence of`
  line `any vacancy or vacancies among its members.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (28541)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28541&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against`
  line `any officer or employee of the University for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act or the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (28542)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Mode of proof of University record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28542&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `A copy of any receipt, application, notice, order,`
  line `proceedings, resolution of any authority or committee of the University, or other documents in the`
  line `possession of the University, or any entry in any register duly maintained by the University, if certified by`
  line `the Registrar so designated shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872`
  line `(1 of 1872) or in any other law for the time being in force, be admitted as evidence of the matters and`
  line `transactions specified therein, where the original thereof would, if produced, have been admissible in`
  line evidence.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (28543)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28543&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Gazette of India, make such provisions, not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appears to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (28544)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Transitional provisions`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28544&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act and the Statutes:--`
  line
  line `(a) The first Vice-Chancellor, the first Registrars and the first Finance Officer shall be`
  line `appointed by the Visitor and they shall be governed by the terms and conditions of service`
  line `specified by the Statutes:`
  line
  line `Provided that the first Vice-Chancellor shall be eligible for appointment in the manner`
  line `specified in the Statutes for another term;`
  line
  line `(b) The first Board of Management shall consist of not more than fifteen members who shall`
  line `be nominated by the Visitor and they shall hold office for a term of three years; and`
  line
  line `(c) (i) The first Planning Board shall consist of not more than ten members who shall be`
  line `nominated by the Visitor and they shall hold office for a term of three years;`
  line
  line `(ii) The Planning Board shall, in addition to the powers and functions conferred on it by this`
  line `Act, exercise the powers of the Academic Council, until the Academic Council is constituted`
  line `under the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, and in the exercise of such powers, the Planning`
  line `Board may co-opt such members as it may decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (28545)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Statutes, Ordinances and Regulations to be published in the Official Gazette and to be laid before Parliament`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539&sectionId=28545&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00020_198550_1517807325539
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be published`
  line `in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making`
  line `any modification in the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation or both Houses agree that the Statute, Ordinance`
  line `or Regulation should not be made, the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
